# OpenPill Python Backend Standards

- Keep runtime behavior backward compatible by default:
  - Preserve env var fallback chains.
  - Avoid breaking API/MCP response fields unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer explicit safe defaults:
  - Experimental features should be default-off.
  - Cost-sensitive/external-model behavior must be opt-in.
- For retrieval and scoring logic:
  - Add metrics fields when useful for observability.
  - Keep ranking deterministic and bounded.
- For policy/guard logic:
  - Fail safely to local behavior instead of hard-failing.
  - Include machine-readable reason fields when routing decisions change.
- Testing discipline:
  - Add or update focused tests for changed behavior.
  - If OpenAPI changes intentionally, update hash snapshot test in the same change.
- Keep modules readable:
  - Prefer small helper functions over deeply nested inline logic.
  - Add brief comments only where logic is non-obvious.
